Subject: Re: [T2] CV joints on VW Bus: changing the allen key

I forgot to add that Porsche 911 cv bolts are the same grade 10.9 black oxidized bolts VW used although the dimensions changed slightly over the years.

On Wednesday, September 03, 2003, at 11:25AM, I wrote:

>The original bolts are 10.9 and that's all that's required to handle the torque from the stock engine. That size/style fastener is more commonly found in the 12.9 grade which is why your kit probably came with them.

